(2,	'Jupiter Retrograde in Taurus',	'jupiter-retrograde-in-taurus-1',	'public/storage/images/blog_531751543071.png',	NULL,	'<p>As&nbsp;<strong>Jupiter</strong>&nbsp;begins its&nbsp;<strong>retrograde journey in Taurus</strong>, you&#39;re finally going to get that much-needed pause.&nbsp;<br />\r\nIt&#39;s good news because it&#39;s a time to reflect on what truly holds value in our lives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most people, when they hear the name retrograde, they shake with fear as the worry blocks their minds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This may be true otherwise, but when you look at your life from the glasses of&nbsp;<strong>Vedic astrology</strong>, you&#39;ll understand that retrograde is not a time to fear, but a powerful opportunity to revisit your relationship with&nbsp;<strong>wealth</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>stability</strong>, and&nbsp;<strong>inner growth</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s a time to find out if you are truly aligned with your dharma or if material comforts have led you off course.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn Vedic astrology, Jupiter is the planet of growth, abundance, wisdom, and higher learning. But when Jupiter goes into retrograde, its forward momentum slows down, inviting us to focus inward.</p>',	87,	'Astroway pro',	'2024-10-22 00:00:00',	1,	0,	'2024-10-22 15:40:48',	'2025-10-31 21:00:28',	1,	1,	'png',	NULL),
(3,	'Ganesh Chaturthi 2024: Dates, Muhurta, and 5 Life-Changing Practices',	'ganesh-chaturthi-2024-dates-muhurta-and-5-life-changing-practices',	'public/storage/images/blog_541751542310.jpg',	NULL,	'<p>According to the Hindu calendar, Ganesh Chaturthi is celebrated in the month of&nbsp;<strong>Bhadra</strong>.Besides His birthday, this 10-day to 12-day festival marks the rejuvenation of our dormant spiritual instincts.Devotees willingly dedicate themselves to the lord&rsquo;s service and prayers. The celebration takes place in August and September.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>According to the English calendar, in 2024, Ganesh Chaturthi begins on September 7th.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The festival&#39;s last day is followed by the immersion of Shri Ganesha&rsquo;s idol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This day is famously called the&nbsp;<strong>Anant Chaturdashi</strong>, it falls&nbsp;<strong>on September 17th</strong>&nbsp;this year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The immersion of His idol in the waters signifies the dissolution of obstructions and egos. Anant Chaturdashi thus not only marks the end of the festival but also symbolizes the culmination of spiritual perfection.</p>',	98,	'Astroway pro',	'2024-10-22 00:00:00',	1,	0,	'2024-10-22 15:48:03',	'2025-10-31 21:01:51',	1,	1,	'jpg',	NULL),
(4,	'9 Names of Shri Krishna and the Stories Behind Them Shri Krishna  loved deities of Sanatan Dharma',	'9-names-of-shri-krishna-and-the-stories-behind-them-shri-krishna-loved-deities-of-sanatan-dharma-1',	'public/storage/images/blog_551752043771.jpg',	NULL,	'<p>But have you ever thought why there are so many names to call&nbsp;<strong>Krishna</strong>? Is it because of the deep emotions and coincidences that the supreme lord, in his 8th human life, has played a central role in many stories.Could the stories and the names be correlated?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The answer is Yes.<br />\r\nRight from&nbsp;<strong>Krishna</strong>, which is the first and birth name of&nbsp;<strong>Shri Vishnu&#39;s</strong>&nbsp;8th Avatar on the Earth to names like&nbsp;<strong>Jagannath</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Purnapurushottam</strong>&nbsp;- every name has a reason and a story to tell.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While it is not possible to cover all the stories and names of&nbsp;<strong>Shri Krishna</strong>&nbsp;here in one blog, we have picked out 9 names of&nbsp;<strong>Lord Krishna</strong>&nbsp;and the anecdotes behind them. Learn why&nbsp;<strong>Shri Hari</strong>&nbsp;has those names and let your love, affection, and devotion for him get even deeper.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And oh, by the way, while we&#39;re talking about&nbsp;<strong>Lord Krishna</strong>, we would like to remind you that&nbsp;<strong>Krishna Janmashtami</strong>&nbsp;is just around the corner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Shri Krishna</strong>&nbsp;was born on the&nbsp;<strong>eighth day</strong>&nbsp;of the&nbsp;<strong>waning moon</strong>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<strong>month of Bhadrapada</strong>&nbsp;under the&nbsp;<strong>Rohini Nakshatra</strong>, and his time of birth was at midnight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Typically, according to the Georgian calendar, this day falls between&nbsp;<strong>August</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>September</strong>. This year,&nbsp;<strong>Janmashtami</strong>&nbsp;falls on&nbsp;<strong>26th August 2024, Monday</strong>.</p>',	177,	'Astroway pro',	'2024-10-22 00:00:00',	1,	0,	'2024-10-22 15:50:23',	'2025-11-04 15:38:46',	1,	1,	'jpg',	'public/storage/images/blogpreview_551732098884.png'),
